  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then take your <strong>chicken </strong>out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Chop your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-sized pieces, then add them to a baking tray (or two!) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up and put the tray[s] in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crisp – these are your <strong>crispy potatoes</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1590501897054-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1590501897054-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1590501897054-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1590501897054-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1590501897054-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Soak your <strong>skewers</strong> in <strong>cold water</strong> (this stops them from burning whilst cooking!)</p><p>Deseed your<strong> pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> roughly, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1590501904140-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1590501904140-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1590501904140-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1590501904140-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1590501904140-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> pepper strips</strong>,<strong> sliced onion</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, then cook for 2 min or until starting to soften </p><p>Once softened, reduce the heat to low and cook for 10 min or until caramelised</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1590501910463-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1590501910463-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1590501910463-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1590501910463-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1590501910463-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut your <strong>chicken breast portion[s]</strong> into 2 strips per person, lengthways</p><p>Place the <strong>chicken strips</strong> in a large mixing bowl with your <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>,<strong> </strong>mix well to ensure the strips are coated</p><p>Thread each <strong>coated</strong> <strong>chicken strip</strong> onto a <strong>soaked</strong> <strong>skewer</strong> in a snake-like fashion and set aside</p>",
